 245:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****     *** Callback registration ***
 246:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****     =============================================
 247:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****     [..]
 248:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****       The compilation define  USE_HAL_DAC_REGISTER_CALLBACKS when set to 1
 249:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****       allows the user to configure dynamically the driver callbacks.
 250:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c **** 
 251:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****     Use Functions HAL_DAC_RegisterCallback() to register a user callback,
 252:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****       it allows to register following callbacks:
 253:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****       (+) ConvCpltCallbackCh1     : callback when a half transfer is completed on Ch1.
 254:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****       (+) ConvHalfCpltCallbackCh1 : callback when a transfer is completed on Ch1.
 255:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****       (+) ErrorCallbackCh1        : callback when an error occurs on Ch1.
 256:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****       (+) DMAUnderrunCallbackCh1  : callback when an underrun error occurs on Ch1.
 257:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****       (+) ConvCpltCallbackCh2     : callback when a half transfer is completed on Ch2.
ARM GAS  /tmp/cc4ENhcr.s 			page 6


 258:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****       (+) ConvHalfCpltCallbackCh2 : callback when a transfer is completed on Ch2.
 259:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****       (+) ErrorCallbackCh2        : callback when an error occurs on Ch2.
 260:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****       (+) DMAUnderrunCallbackCh2  : callback when an underrun error occurs on Ch2.
 261:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****       (+) MspInitCallback         : DAC MspInit.
 262:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****       (+) MspDeInitCallback       : DAC MspdeInit.
 263:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****       This function takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle, the Callback ID
 264:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****       and a pointer to the user callback function.
 265:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c **** 
 266:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****     Use function HAL_DAC_UnRegisterCallback() to reset a callback to the default
 267:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****       weak (surcharged) function. It allows to reset following callbacks:
 268:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****       (+) ConvCpltCallbackCh1     : callback when a half transfer is completed on Ch1.
 269:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****       (+) ConvHalfCpltCallbackCh1 : callback when a transfer is completed on Ch1.
 270:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****       (+) ErrorCallbackCh1        : callback when an error occurs on Ch1.
 271:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****       (+) DMAUnderrunCallbackCh1  : callback when an underrun error occurs on Ch1.
 272:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****       (+) ConvCpltCallbackCh2     : callback when a half transfer is completed on Ch2.
 273:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****       (+) ConvHalfCpltCallbackCh2 : callback when a transfer is completed on Ch2.
 274:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****       (+) ErrorCallbackCh2        : callback when an error occurs on Ch2.
 275:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****       (+) DMAUnderrunCallbackCh2  : callback when an underrun error occurs on Ch2.
 276:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****       (+) MspInitCallback         : DAC MspInit.
 277:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****       (+) MspDeInitCallback       : DAC MspdeInit.
 278:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****       (+) All Callbacks
 279:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****       This function) takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle and the Callback ID.
 280:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c **** 
 281:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****       By default, after the HAL_DAC_Init and if the state is HAL_DAC_STATE_RESET
 282:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****       all callbacks are reset to the corresponding legacy weak (surcharged) functions.
 283:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****       Exception done for MspInit and MspDeInit callbacks that are respectively
 284:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****       reset to the legacy weak (surcharged) functions in the HAL_DAC_Init
 285:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****       and HAL_DAC_DeInit only when these callbacks are null (not registered beforehand).
 286:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****       If not, MspInit or MspDeInit are not null, the HAL_DAC_Init and HAL_DAC_DeInit
 287:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****       keep and use the user MspInit/MspDeInit callbacks (registered beforehand)
 288:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c **** 
 289:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****       Callbacks can be registered/unregistered in READY state only.
 290:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****       Exception done for MspInit/MspDeInit callbacks that can be registered/unregistered
 291:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****       in READY or RESET state, thus registered (user) MspInit/DeInit callbacks can be used
 292:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****       during the Init/DeInit.
 293:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****       In that case first register the MspInit/MspDeInit user callbacks
 294:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****       using HAL_DAC_RegisterCallback before calling HAL_DAC_DeInit
 295:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****       or HAL_DAC_Init function.
 296:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c **** 
 297:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****       When The compilation define USE_HAL_DAC_REGISTER_CALLBACKS is set to 0 or
 298:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****       not defined, the callback registering feature is not available
 299:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c ****       and weak (surcharged) callbacks are used.
 300:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_dac.c **** 
